      h3 A Brief Summary
      sub 
        br 
        | The Node.JS app is deployed as a versioned container on Google App Engine(Cloud Storage Buckets). The app UI/UX is mobile-friendly & adaptable across-platforms.  
        br 
        | Express/pug frameworks are implemented to deliver template rendering with functionality to return a json containing all request headers.
        br
        br
        h4
          b Secured/Configured For End-To-End Encryption 
        | All traffic is redirected to HTTPS scheme with enforced HSTS policies and enabled constraints to use the best version of TLS for various traffic. 
        br
        | The Cloudflare Origin CA certificate is installed on the app server; ensuring full encryption of traffic secured with Elliptic Curve algorithms. The root ca is signed by a trusted and verified Google provided root authority.
        br 
        | Firewall rules have been configured on both CloudFlare and GCP to control traffic via filters based on cookies, location, IP address, user agent, URI, and more.
        br
        br
        h4
          b Availability/Performance 
        | Argo Smart Routing and Tiered Caching have been enabled and additional health checks are configured to monitor the availability, security, performance of the origin server.
        br
        | Despite minifying some of the assets of the view in the NodeJS, CloudFlare is also enabled to resize, optimize and preload/prefetch images and other resources. 
